About MIT Open Scholarship
Access open research, scholarship, and institutional publications from MIT — peer-reviewed articles, theses and dissertations, technical reports, working papers, task force reports, annual reports, teaching resources, and archived OpenCourseWare materials. Most items are openly accessible to anyone. For a broader search across all library systems including articles, books, archival finding aids, research guides, databases, geospatial data, and more, try Search MIT Libraries.
\n
MIT community members can log in to submit works to the repository by using MyDSpace from their account menu. Read more in our guide.
